      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 physical constructs were tested across two independent laboratories, exceeding the minimum sample size for Gradation 3. Traceability to specific lot numbers and dimensional inspection records was maintained."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single axial compressive load condition per ASTM F1717. While this condition is standardised and clinically relevant, the absence of additional load configurations (e.g., torsion, lateral bending) limits the achieved gradation to 2, one below the required level. This gap is acknowledged as a residual uncertainty."
    },
    {
