      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "The quantities of interest — construct stiffness and yield load — are directly specified in ASTM F1717 and are the primary metrics used in regulatory submissions for spinal fixation systems. Their clinical and regulatory relevance is well established."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "The validation activities replicate the exact ASTM F1717 test configuration that constitutes the intended use of the model. Hardware geometry, loading mode, and boundary conditions in the FEA mirror those of the physical test, providing high relevance."
